 Nigeria has recorded 39 new cases of COVID-19 bringing the total number of persons who have tested positive in the country to 167,142 The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) announced this via its website https://covid19.ncdc.gov.ng/ on Friday morning, June 18, 2021. According to NCDC; “The 39 new cases are reported from 6 states- Lagos (34), Ebonyi (1), Ekiti (1), FCT (1), Jigawa (1), Rivers (1),” READ ALSO: FG Reopens First Dose COVID-19 Vaccination, Says Second Dose To End June 25 The NCDC also added that as of 17 June, 167,142 cases had been confirmed, 163,535 cases treated and discharged, while 2,117 deaths were recorded. The post COVID-19: Nigeria Confirms 39 New Cases appeared first on Information Nigeria.